e or the history that is lived and written about. In the same entry, he stated that the "doctrines" that this systematic theology would attempt to understand are focused on "redemption." The seeds of such a theology are planted in the current volume, where the formulae that are so pronounced in his later work first appear. Students of Lonergan’s work will find their understanding of his philosophy profoundly affected by the essays in this volume.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aEducationxPhilosophy. 0aPhilosophy. 0aTheology. 7aRELIGION / Theology.2bisacsh  aBernard Lonergan.  aDialectic of history.  aGeschichte.  aGregorian University.  aPhilosophy.  aProgress.  adecline.  ahistory of religion.  ahistory.  amethod in theology.  aredemption.  asystematic theology.  atheology.1 aDadosky, John , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDoran, S.J., Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishz978311061074108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2019z9783110606508oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065206240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753426440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487534264423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487534264.jpg  a978-3-11-061074-1  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE